    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 7, 2026\n\n---\n\n## ⏰ Trump Gives Iran Until Tuesday Night to Reopen Hormuz. Iran Says No.\n\nDay 38 of the Iran war just got a hard deadline attached to it.\n\n- **The ultimatum:** Trump announced at a White House press conference that Iran has until Tuesday 8:00 PM ET to reopen the Strait of Hormuz or face destruction of power plants and bridges. Defense Secretary Hegseth confirmed these are the most intensive U.S.-Israeli strikes since the conflict began.\n- **The rejection:** Iran formally turned down a Pakistan-brokered 45-day ceasefire proposal, instead presenting a 10-clause counter-proposal demanding permanent cessation, lifting of all sanctions, regional peace protocols, and reconstruction commitments. The gap between \"45-day pause\" and \"permanent settlement with guarantees\" is not subtle.\n\n*The White House wants a temporary truce. Iran wants a peace treaty. The difference is roughly the size of a war.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/liveblog/2026/4/7/iran-war-live-trump-warns-of-devastating-attacks-as-deal-deadline-nears) | [Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-06/iran-rejects-ceasefire-before-trump-ultimatum-expires-on-hormuz) | [NPR](https://www.npr.org/2026/04/06/nx-s1-5774449/trump-sets-deadline-for-iran-to-reopen-the-strait-of-hormuz)\n\n---\n\n## ⚖️ The Supreme Court Blew Up Trump's Tariff Authority. He Attacked His Own Justices.\n\nThe Supreme Court's February ruling that IEEPA doesn't authorize presidential tariffs just became very expensive. Also very personal.\n\n- **The ruling:** The 6-3 February decision invalidated Trump's emergency tariff authority, potentially opening $166 billion in refund claims across 333,000+ importers. The administration pivoted to Section 122 and 301 of the Trade Act to reimpose duties — extending trade uncertainty indefinitely.\n- **The reaction:** Trump publicly called Justices Barrett and Gorsuch — both his nominees — \"sickening\" for joining the majority. The administration is doubling down on tariffs anyway, using alternative legal authorities, while Supreme Court challenges to the new architecture are already being filed.\n\n*Trump appointed two of the six justices who ruled against him. He is not pleased. They are, presumably, also not pleased.*\n\n**Sources:** [Skadden](https://www.skadden.com/insights/publications/2026/02/the-supreme-court-ends-ieepa-tariffs) | [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/03/26/trump-supreme-court-tariffs-barrett-gorsuch-trade-ieepa-ruling.html) | [SCOTUSblog](https://www.scotusblog.com/2026/03/the-remaining-questions-after-the-supreme-courts-tariffs-ruling/)\n\n---\n\n## 🛩️ Russia Hit Odesa With 1,000+ Drones Last Week. Ukraine Hit a Russian Frigate.\n\nThe spring offensive is underway and neither side is pulling its punches.\n\n- **The Russian push:** Russia launched 1,000+ drones, 1,350+ guided bombs, and 40+ missiles at Ukraine in a single week. Three killed in Odesa, including a child. 340,000 homes in Chernihiv Oblast lost power overnight after strikes on energy infrastructure.\n- **The Ukrainian response:** Ukraine struck back with a drone attack setting the Sheskharis oil terminal ablaze and targeting a Russian frigate in Novorossiysk. Also: Russia's mobile internet has been blacked out in Moscow since March 7 — apparently to prevent Ukrainian drone coordination. Cool solution.\n\n*Both sides are escalating. The peace negotiations are \"90–95% complete.\" Those two facts are doing a lot of work simultaneously.*\n\n**Sources:** [Empr.media](https://empr.media/news/war/russia-ukraine-war-updates-key-developments-as-of-april-3-2026/) | [Russia Matters](https://www.russiamatters.org/news/russia-ukraine-war-report-card/russia-ukraine-war-report-card-april-1-2026)\n\n---\n\n## 🕊️ Trump and Zelensky Are 90–95% Agreed on Ukraine Peace. The Other 5% Involves Russia.\n\nA significant diplomatic breakthrough in the Ukraine war — conditional on whether the party doing the invading agrees.\n\n- **The alignment:** U.S. and Ukrainian officials report Trump and Zelensky have reached 90–95% agreement on a peace framework after months of friction. This is the closest the two countries have come to a joint position.\n- **The obstacle:** Russia is currently conducting its most intensive spring offensive since the war began. Moscow's internet blackout is a deliberate military countermeasure. The Kremlin has not been asked yet whether it would like to stop winning territory in exchange for a framework it didn't negotiate.\n\n*Getting two of the three parties to agree on a peace deal for a war being fought by all three is a start. A start.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNN](https://www.cnn.com/world/europe/ukraine) | [Global Security](https://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/war/russo-ukraine-2026-04-01.htm)\n\n---\n\n## 🤝 The Trump-Xi Summit Produced \"Progress.\" Nobody Can Quite Define It.\n\nTrump visited Beijing March 31–April 2. Both sides called it productive. The issues that caused the tensions remain unresolved.\n\n- **What happened:** Commitments to continued rare earth mineral access for U.S. buyers, a ceasefire extension, and a framework for further AI chip export control talks. The SCOTUS IEEPA ruling — which struck down much of Trump's tariff authority before the summit — meaningfully weakened U.S. negotiating leverage.\n- **What didn't:** China's structural trade imbalance, clear AI chip export rules, and tech sector access remain unresolved. The Atlantic Council describes the outcomes as \"stabilizing but not transformative.\"\n\n*A summit that produced a framework for future talks about a framework. Diplomacy, everyone.*\n\n**Sources:** [World Policy Hub](https://worldpolicyhub.com/u-s-china-summit-2026-strategic-stakes-trade-and-tech-at-the-forefront/) | [Atlantic Council](https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/new-atlanticist/experts-react/experts-react-what-does-the-trump-xi-meeting-mean-for-trade-technology-security-and-beyond/)"
